This paper focuses on the task of geolocating Twitter users, which involves natural language processing, social media analysis, and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the applications of geolocation in managing natural crises and public health, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential biases in geographic distribution, which is relevant to cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
